Authored-by: Marcin FM <marcin@lgic.pl>

Fedora packages the pinned ICU component as a private PDFium library. Embed
ICU's data in that library instead of requiring an untracked icudtl.dat file
at runtime.

--- a/third_party/icu/config.gni
+++ b/third_party/icu/config.gni
@@ -12,7 +12,7 @@ else {
   declare_args() {
     # Tells icu to load an external data file rather than rely on the icudata
     # being linked directly into the binary.
-    icu_use_data_file = true
+    icu_use_data_file = false
 
     # If true, then this creates a stub data file. This should be disabled if
     # a custom data file will be used instead, in order to avoid conflicting
